headline: Home Depot (HD) Is Down 5.3% After Cutting 2023 Outlook on Weak Renovation and Housing Demand – Has the Bull Case Changed?
summary: Home Depot recently reported weaker-than-expected third-quarter earnings, missing profit expectations for the third consecutive quarter and lowering its full-year profit outlook due to subdued home improvement demand and economic uncertainty. Management specifically cited postponed major renovation projects, a sluggish housing market, and decreased storm-related product sales as critical drivers behind the reduced guidance and earnings miss.
